Romania Government in Talks with Microsoft Corp's Microsoft Romania over EUR 33 Million Deal-Telecompaper Europe
Wednesday, 19 Dec 2012 07:00pm EST
Telecompaper Europe reported that Romania's Government negotiates a contract with the local branch of Microsoft Corp concerning the use of the Company's software products in public institutions and the education system, writes local paper Ziarul Financiar citing a document from the press office of the Government. The deal could be worth over EUR 33 million. According to the document, the Government discussed during a meeting held on December 18, 2012 a memorandum concerning the state of negotiations with Microsoft Romania concerning the implementation of approved measures during the Government meeting from October 24, 2012 through the memorandum on the subject Measures necessary to use Microsoft licenses in institutions and public education. The government approved the memorandum prepared by the Ministry of Communications and Information, the document said. The document published by the Government shows that following negotiations, the buy out offer was reduced from EUR 45.091 million to EUR 33.254 million. The launch in 2013 of possible new acquisitions to ensure the necessary licenses for local and central public institutions and the education system will be made only after the elaboration of a strategy for the use of software, the document said.Â 
